---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Accessibility Statement - Adam Palencar"
  description="Accessibility commitment and WCAG 2.2 AA conformance details."
>
  <article class="a11y-statement">
    <h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>

    <h2>Commitment</h2>
    <p>I am committed to making this website accessible to everyone, including people with disabilities. I aim to conform to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2 at Level AA.</p>

    <h2>Conformance Status</h2>
    <p>This website is partially conformant with WCAG 2.2 Level AA. "Partially conformant" means that some parts of the content may not fully conform to the standard.</p>

    <h2>Measures Taken</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Semantic HTML landmarks throughout (header, nav, main, footer)</li>
      <li>Logical heading hierarchy with no skipped levels</li>
      <li>Keyboard-navigable interface with visible focus states</li>
      <li>Sufficient color contrast ratios (4.5:1 body text, 3:1 large text)</li>
      <li>Skip-to-content link for keyboard users</li>
      <li>Responsive design tested at multiple breakpoints</li>
      <li>Reduced motion support via prefers-reduced-motion media query</li>
      <li>Alt text provided for all meaningful images</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Known Limitations</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Some third-party tool icons in the About page tools section may lack detailed alt text descriptions</li>
      <li>PDF resume may not be fully screen-reader accessible</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Feedback</h2>
    <p>If you encounter any accessibility barriers on this site, please contact me. I take accessibility feedback seriously and will do my best to address issues promptly. <a href="mailto:adampalencar25@gmail.com">adampalencar25@gmail.com</a></p>

    <h2>Assessment</h2>
    <p>This statement was last updated on April 2026. Self-assessment was performed against WCAG 2.2 Level AA criteria.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  @layer components {
    .a11y-statement {
      max-width: 720px;
      margin-inline: auto;
      padding: var(--space-7) var(--grid-gutter) var(--space-8);
    }

    .a11y-statement h2 {
      margin-top: var(--space-6);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    }

    .a11y-statement p {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    }

    .a11y-statement ul {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      padding-left: var(--space-4);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    }

    .a11y-statement li {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    }

    .a11y-statement a {
      color: var(--accent);
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  }
</style>
